ous language and culture continuance current revitalization efforts hold.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEducation, BilingualzUnited States. 0aIndians of North AmericaxEducationxPlanning. 0aIndians of North AmericaxEducation. 0aIndians of North AmericaxLanguagesxRevival. 0aIndians of North AmericaxLanguagesxSocial aspects. 0aIntercultural communication. 0aLanguage planningxUnited States. 0aLanguage planningzUnited States. 0aLanguage policyxUnited States. 0aLanguage policyzUnited States. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aIndigenous language.  aNative America.  alanguage education.  alanguage planning.  alanguage policy.1 aGamble, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLittlebear, Richard E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarty, Teresa L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomero-Little, Mary Eunice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarhol, Larisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZepeda, Ofelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769864340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847698643423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847698643/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL